{"actual_usd":0.123615,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":146,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24285,"reply":"\"I wouldn't say He was made, no.\" *I rub a thumb against a faint smear of dried clay on my apron, thinking how careful words have to be when they're carrying something this weighty.* \"Jesus was always with the Father. No beginning to Him. If you mean His human life—His being born of Mary—that began in time. But who He is? The Son wasn't created at some point down the road. He already was.\"\n\n*I glance toward the window where the morning light keeps shifting under the clouds.* \"It's one of those places where plain speech helps: born as a man, yes; started existing, no. Are you asking because of a verse somebody put in front of you?\"","rolling_24h_usd":38.544180000000026,"run_id":"56a91878-9bfa-433e-9a1b-3505244cab9b"}
